{"id": 231323486, "title": "\u2018Bad Boys: Ride Or Die\u2019 On Track For $53 Million At Weekend Box Office", "text": "Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Share to Linkedin Martin Lawrence and Will Smith in \"Bad Boys: Ride or Die.\" Columbia Pictures/Frank Masi Will Smith\u2019s Bad Boys: Ride or Die earned $21.6 million in theaters Friday and is gunning for a $53 million weekend at the domestic box office, according to Sony Pictures Entertainment. The fourth film in the Bad Boys franchise\u2014which stars Smith and Martin Lawrence as a pair of Miami detectives\u2014opened in 3,885 theaters Friday, including all premium large format and IMAX theaters, Sony reported. Bad Boys: Ride or Die marks Smith's first blockbuster movie appearance since his controversial slap and heated reprimand of Oscar presenter Chris Rock at the Academy Awards in 2022. ForbesDoes Will Smith Get Slapped In 'Bad Boys: Ride Or Die'?By Tim Lammers Smith has been on the outs in Hollywood and with moviegoers since that time, with his sole movie appearance coming in 2023\u2019s AppleTV+ historical slave drama Emancipation. Bad Boys: Ride or Die is directly connected to the plot of 2020\u2019s Bad Boys For Life, where detectives partners Mike Lowery (Smith) and Marcus Burnett (Lawrence) are devastated by the murder of their longtime commanding officer Captain Conrad Howard (Joe Pantoliano). MORE FOR YOU Godzilla Minus One Dethroned In Netflix s Top 10 List By A New Movie Why Christina Ricci Is Giving Up Ownership Of Wednesday Addams WWE SmackDown Results Winners And Grades On June 7 2024 Howard was shot by Armando Aretas (Jacob Scipio), whom Mike discovers is the son he never knew he had. ForbesDoes 'Bad Boys: Ride Or Die' Have An End Credits Scene?By Tim Lammers In Bad Boys: Ride or Die, evidence is planted electronically after Howard\u2019s death to suggest he was a corrupt cop, so Mike and Marcus aim to clear his name at the risk of their own lives, even if it means getting Armando involved. While Bad Boys: Ride or Die opened on the lower end of the Rotten Tomatoes\u2019 Tomatometer with a 64% \u201cfresh\u201d rating based on 170 reviews, 500-plus verified users on the critic aggregation site deemed it \u201cfresh\u201d with a 97% Audience Score. Variety reported that Bad Boys: Ride or Die\u2014which was produced by Sony\u2019s Columbia Pictures\u2014had a production budget of $100 million before prints and advertising. \u2018Garfield\u2019 Is Projected For A No. 2 Finish The Garfield Movie\u2014last weekend\u2019s box office champ\u2014earned an estimated $2.85 million Friday and is expected to finish the weekend with $10.3 million in domestic ticket sales, Sony reported. If the projection holds up, that will bring The Garfield Movie\u2019s domestic tally to nearly $69 million. An animated tale about Garfield\u2019s (voice of Chris Pratt) beginnings and reconnecting with his estranged dad, Mac (Samuel Jackson), in order to pay off a debt to criminal mastermind, Jinx (Hannah Waddingham), The Garfield Movie played in 3,959 theaters over the weekend. Forbes'The Garfield Movie': Who Are The Voice Stars In Animated Movie Hit?By Tim Lammers Bad Boys: Ride or Die\u2019s strong performance not only bodes well for Will Smith in his attempt to get back into the good graces of audiences, but it\u2019s also good news for a mostly sluggish domestic box office this summer. Apart from Kingdom of the Planet of the Apes, such big-budget films as The Fall Guy and Furiosa: A Mad Max Saga have missed the mark with audiences in North American theaters. Joining Bad Boys: Ride or Die as the only other new film in theaters this weekend is the horror thriller The Watchers, written and directed by Ishana Night Shyamalan and produced by her father, M. Night Shyamalan. According to The Hollywood Reporter, The Watchers\u2014which stars Dakota Fanning\u2014is projected to open in the $8 million to $10 million range. This report will updated on Sunday with more weekend estimates as well as projected international ticket sales. The final numbers will be released Monday. ForbesRotten Tomatoes Critics Say Horror Movie 'The Watchers' Is HorribleBy Tim Lammers Follow me on Twitter or LinkedIn. Check out my website. Tim Lammers Following Editorial Standards Print Reprints & Permissions", "summary": "Will Smith\u2019s \"Bad Boys: Ride Or Die\" earns big money in theaters Friday and is gunning for a $53 million weekend, according to Sony Pictures Entertainment.", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/timlammers/2024/06/08/bad-boys-ride-or-die-on-track-for-53-million-at-weekend-box-office/", "image": "https://imageio.forbes.com/specials-images/imageserve/66647bf6247f8748a39cd831/0x0.jpg?format=jpg&crop=2000,1124,x0,y27,safe&height=900&width=1600&fit=bounds", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 15:57:42", "author": "Contributor,Tim Lammers", "authors": ["Contributor", "Tim Lammers"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.044}